  "body": "When implementing `mint` function of an ERC777 that simply calls the [internal `_mint` function](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/c789941d76dd713333bdeafe5b4484f6d9543c4e/contracts/token/ERC777/ERC777.sol#L307), currently one cannot opt out from the `requireReceptionAck` which is internally hard-coded to `true`. This is different from e.g. [`_send`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/c789941d76dd713333bdeafe5b4484f6d9543c4e/contracts/token/ERC777/ERC777.sol#L341). As a consequence, smart contracts (e.g. multisigs) cannot mint tokens for themselves, even when registered in the ERC1820 registry unless they implement the target function - but neither Gnosis Safe not Gnosis Wallet do implement that so it would be really useful to implement a `mint` function which disables the `requireReceptionAck` or pass `false` by default.",
